The paper focuses on developing a near-memory accelerator for training deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the architecture and control overhead, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
